Whereas a 'morel' is a type of mushroom, a 'moral' is a rather more troublesome specimen. Nearly everybody talks about morality as if they know something well, which may be an obscene lie, a humble admittance of fact, or neither.
     
'''Morality''' refers to the concept of human [[ethics]] which pertains to matters of [[good and evil]] —also referred to as "[[right]] or [[wrong]]", used within three contexts: individual [[conscience]]; systems of [[principle]]s and [[judgment]]s — sometimes called [[moral value]]s —shared within a [[cultural]], [[religion|religious]], [[secular]], [[secular humanism|Humanist]], or [[philosophical]] community; and codes of behavior or [[Code of conduct|conduct]].
